{
  "texts": [
    "Analogously, the formal local system associated with V has graded pieces V 0",
    "for the active circles ⟨ f ⟩ of Θ, and they are determined by vector spaces",
    "For ⟨f ⟩ ∈ I, we will denote by ⟨ f ⟩ its Legendre transform and denote by ℓ f: ⟨f ⟩ ∼ → ⟨ f ⟩ the homeomorphism of circles defined by the Legendre transform.",
    "Therefore, the active circles of V are the ⟨ f ⟩ for ⟨f ⟩ ⊂ I an active circle of V.",
    "The following theorem is a reformulation, in our situation and language set up above, of the main result of [Moc25] for the Fourier transform from ∞ to ∞ (see §8.9 and §10.5 in loc. cit.)."
  ]
}